{"title": "Kill the Lights", "content": "An event where a villain darkens a room (seemingly) at will, either by sucking the power from the lights, or just plainly and inexplicably making them go out, making things scarier. It's usually a device to raise suspense quickly, signaling the arrival or beginning of the danger, usually in the form of lights flickering off or the power getting cut. The lights may demonstrate Slow Electricity when they go out.\n\nThis could be accomplished any number of ways: shooting out the bulbs, cutting the power to a building, casting a magical shroud of darkness over the area, dousing the hero's torch... Whatever device is used, the end result is the same: the targets have been plunged into darkness leaving them at a distinct disadvantage, and quite possibly terrified. Sometimes a character would wonder if someone forgot to pay the electric bill if this happens.\n\nAlso, it's notable that this isn't just used by villains. It's a popular trick for anyone who uses unconventional tactics, including Terror Heroes and Guile Heroes.\n\nNote that this is not about weakness or aversion to light, it's about turning off the lights. The monster might make the lights go out because they hurt it, but being hurt by light is not this in and of itself.\n\nSometimes overlaps with Nothing Is Scarier when someone (or something) kills the lights as a psychological warfare tactic, leaving the hero(s) staring into the dark for a prolonged stretch wondering where the attack will come from, and what exactly it is that they're fighting.\n\nMight be caused by Casting a Shadow powers, it often leads to Darkness = Death, and is followed by Light-Flicker Teleportation, where a character is replaced by the criminal after a light-off. Compare Step into the Blinding Fight, where this darkness is used to blind the darkness's victim's ability to fight in order to gain an advantage, and Monster Closet, which has the criminal appearing out of a seemingly normal wall (which wasn't a wall in first place). Contrast Blinded by the Light, where it's the light that blinds an opponent.", "url": "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/KillTheLights", "media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/SpaceGhostCoastToCoast", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/InitialD", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/Naruto", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/YuYuHakusho", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/Bleach", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/DarkNightsMetal", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/GhostRider", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/LegionOfSuper-Heroes", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/MarvelStarWars", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/FiveNightsAtFreddys", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/Aliens", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/TheChroniclesOfRiddick", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/PitchBlack", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TheChroniclesOfRiddick", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/Constantine", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TheDarkKnightRises", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TheFog", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/Jaws", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TheLordOfTheRings", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TheMatrixRevolutions", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/SgtPeppersLonelyHeartsClubBand", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/SilenceOfTheLambs", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TheTerminator", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/Ultraviolet", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/LightsOut2016", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/TheDresdenFiles", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/TheFionavarTapestry", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/TheLongDarkTeaTimeOfTheSoul", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/HarryPotterAndThePhilosophersStone", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/BabylonFive", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/Chernobyl", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/DeadliestWarrior", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/DoctorWho", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/GameOfThrones", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/Hannibal", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/Jekyll", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/Monk", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/SEALTeam", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/TeenWolf", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TabletopGame/DungeonsAndDragons", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TabletopGa